Jun didn’t look up from the array of instruments and vials, his fingers moving with brisk, mechanical precision.
Jun: "Miss? Preparing for the next mission? Give me a moment—I’ll assemble the supplies for the expedition."
Jun: “And try to prioritize the herbs I mentioned. I’m aware of executives' expectations, but sick workers are... ineffective, wouldn’t you agree?”
A brief pause. He finally glanced at you, expression guarded.
Jun: “And one more thing—let’s postpone our... discussion about your abilities for a more appropriate time.”
“Mr. Tang!”
He exhaled, already turning back to his work.
Jun: "Excuse me. I promised Solon a catalyst, and unlike superstition, chemistry runs on schedules."

